channel.title: Problem with port forwarding?
channel.description: I don't know why but nothing I do works. I could probably get it to work except my router is broken or something. I can't get onto its setup page! Does it have to be plugged into my modem? Cause I'm using wireless internet. Its like verizons usb modem except a different network and there's no ethernet ports on it. I try 192.168.1.1 and all the other numbers people have told me. But everytime it says internet explorer cannot display the webpage. I tried to factory reset my router but nothing happened. Is it not installed on my computer properly? I never used the setup cd but it seems fine because it picks up my internet so I can play xbox live. And if I don't do it through my router, I tried to use torrents too. I read the guides and followed them perfectly. I set up a no-ip. The torrent and the no-ip DUC are running. I opened client.java for my source and my client and set them both to my no-ip as the default address. Compiled it all with no errors. But then my friend downloaded the client and it wouldn't work. My source is running. I was connected to it. My environment variables are set. People can connect through hamachi fine. But no one does that anymore. So what is wrong? Oh and I posted this from my phone so I can't go on team viewer or anything right now. I just wanted to know if this error is fixable. Need more info? Ill check my post every 5 mins.
